Objective

Design and implement a Python-based fitness and health calculator that enables users to:

- Calculate their Body Mass Index (BMI) and identify health category (Underweight, Healthy, Overweight, Obese)
- Compute Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) and Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) based on user input and established equations
- Recommend daily protein, fat, and carbohydrate intake using calorie needs and standard nutritional guidelines
- Deliver actionable health and fitness advice tailored to each user's BMI category

